  "ExecutionTrace": [
    "Step 0: Idle",
    "Step 1: Thinking\n  [{ Id = 2ef266ad-d4f5-41ff-bfed-1cc044dddff4\n     CorrelationId = CorrelationId b9639d14-434d-4ee2-8d49-0279b56b0c8a\n     Sender = System\n     Receiver = Some (Agent (AgentId 6d7e52d9-2ae0-4c65-8220-f725c89b4ffb))\n     Performative = Request\n     Intent = Some Coding\n     Constraints = { MaxTokens = None\n                     MaxComplexity = None\n                     Timeout = None\n                     KnowledgeBoundary = [] }\n     Ontology = None\n     Language = \u0022text\u0022\n     Content =\n      \u0022### Summary of Task and Constraints\n\n**Task**: Implement a simple text summarization tool using F#.\n\n**Constraints**:\n- The tool should take a string input.\n- It must output a summary of the text.\n- Use natural language processing techniques.\n\n**Validation Criteria**: \n- The tool should accurately summarize various test texts, demonstrating understanding of key points and context.\n\n### Available Tools\n\nThe available tools include:\n- \u0060fetch_webpage\u0060: Fetches a webpage and extracts readable text content.\n- \u0060fsharp_eval\u0060: Evaluates F# code using F# Interactive.\n- \u0060summarize\u0060: Summarizes the given text.\n\n### Steps to Implement the Text Summarization Tool\n\n1. **Fetch Webpage Content**: Use the \u0060fetch_webpage\u0060 tool to fetch the webpage and extract readable text content.\n2. **Summarize Text**: Use the \u0060summarize\u0060 tool to generate a summary of the fetched text.\n\n### Detailed Implementation\n\n#### Step 1: Fetch Webpage Content\nTo fetch the webpage content, we need to provide the URL of the webpage we want to summarize.\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060fsharp\nlet url = \u0022https://example.com\u0022\nlet response = http_get { url = url }\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\nThis will return the text content of the webpage.\n\n#### Step 2: Summarize Text\nOnce we have the text content, we can use the \u0060summarize\u0060 tool to generate a summary.\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060fsharp\nlet summary = summarize { text = response.text }\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n### Final Solution\n\nThe final solution involves fetching the webpage content and then summarizing it using the available tools.\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060fsharp\nlet url = \u0022https://example.com\u0022\nlet response = http_get { url = url }\n\nlet summary = summarize { text = response.text }\n\n// Output the summary\nprintfn \u0022%s\u0022 summary\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n### Explanation of Steps\n\n1. **Fetching Webpage Content**:\n   - Use \u0060http_get\u0060 to fetch the webpage content.\n   - The URL is provided as input to the \u0060http_get\u0060 tool.\n\n2. **Summarizing Text**:\n   - Use \u0060summarize\u0060 to generate a summary of the fetched text.\n   - The fetched text is passed as input to the \u0060summarize\u0060 tool.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nThe task involves implementing a simple text summarization tool using F#. By fetching the webpage content and then summarizing it, we can achieve the goal. The final solution demonstrates how to use the available tools to accomplish this task effectively.\u0022\n     Timestamp = 2025-12-28 8:12:51 AM\n     Metadata = map [] }]",
